      "message": "I think L480 is checking literally for the word \"struct.\"\n\nThis check is, AFAICS, checking to see if we have a struct name immediately followed by a semicolon. Like, assuming struct Foo {} exists, then a declaration that\u0027s just `Foo;`\n\nWhich, I don\u0027t know why this is a thing we check for? But there isn\u0027t a unit test for it either...?? Could you add a test like this and see what happens?",
